ADD START_SCREEN_VOID_DWELLERS_SOL:0 "To most, the vacuum of space is a hostile environment to be conquered or overcome. To us, it is home. For thousands of years, our species has resided on three space stations, each orbiting a different planet in our dilapidated solar system. Whether they were built by our ancestors or someone else, we do not know.\n\nAlthough our biology would suggest that our species at some point originated on a planet, recorded history makes no mention of it. Some speculate that the toxic wasteland of a planet found beneath one of our stations is the lost homeworld of our species, but the truth may never be known.\n\nIt has only been a few centuries since spaceflight allowing travel between our three stations was invented - or rediscovered, depending on who you ask. Suspicion and mistrust gradually gave way to trade and mutual cooperation. By the time of our first hyperdrive, the three habitats had united under one flag."
CN2 START_SCREEN_VOID_DWELLERS_SOL:0 "对于大多数生物，太空中的真空环境不适于生存，需要专门征服或攻克。对我们而言，虚空就是家园。千百年来，我们的物种居住于三个空间站之上，每个环绕着恒星系中一个不同的行星。究竟是我们的祖先还是什么其他人建造了空间站，我们不得而知。\n\n尽管我们的生物学结构暗示我们物种可能在某种程度上起源于一颗行星，有记录的历史却完全没有提到这一点。有些人推测，从我们的一个空间站之下找到的剧毒废土行星就是我们物种失落的家园，但真相或许永远不得而知。\n\n只在几个世纪前，我们才发明了足以在我们三个空间站之间往来的太空旅行方式——又或者叫再发明，取决于你问的人是谁。怀疑和猜忌逐渐让位于贸易和相互合作。在我们的第一台超空间引擎发明之时，三个居住站已经团结在了同一旗帜之下。"
